Description: Rim and neck sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery amphora; perhaps white slip; interior: wide painted band on top of rim and top of neck, above further band; exterior: on rim, short vertical strokes with streaky band below; at top of neck dividing band of strokes above part of meander.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see British Museum 1861,0425.47 (from Camiros), dated about 540 BC (CVA BM 8, pl. 12, 1).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.089)
